            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>On Jan. 22, 1803, William Ball of Frederick County, Va., sold a slave boy, Wilson, age 13, to James Powers, for 80 Pounds U.S. money. The sale was witnessed by William Patton and Charles Bakley or Barkley.</p>
                                 <p>Paul Hardin, University of Illinois Office of Instructional Resources, donated this item to the Survey in 1997.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


